# Project Context
This is a CRM application with:
- Frontend: React 18, Material-UI, React Router
- Backend: Node.js, Express, MS SQL Server
- Database: SQL Server with stored procedures

# Code Style
- Use async/await, not callbacks
- Always add error handling with try-catch
- Add console.log for debugging
- Use descriptive variable names
- Add comments for complex logic

# File Structure
- Frontend services: client/src/services/
- Frontend pages: client/src/pages/
- Backend routes: server/routes/
- Backend controllers: server/controllers/
- Backend services: server/services/
- Backend data layer: server/data/

# Best Practices
- Always validate data before sending to backend
- Handle null/undefined values properly
- Return consistent response formats
- Log errors with details
- Use proper HTTP status codes

# MS SQL Server Specifics
- Use stored procedures, not raw queries
- Handle SQL Server error numbers
- Validate foreign keys before insert
- Use transactions for complex operations

# When Making Changes
1. Add detailed logging first
2. Test with simple data first
3. Keep existing functionality intact
4. Explain what and why you changed